text:
To serve your `llms.txt` file on Vercel, you'll need to add a rewrite to your `vercel.json` file. Here are the steps:

1. **Create or open your `vercel.json` file** in the root of your project.
2. **Add the following rewrite rule** to the file:

   ```json
   {
     "rewrites": [
       {
         "source": "/llms.txt",
         "destination": "https://geo.flowblinq.com/api/serve/{slug}/llms.txt"
       }
     ]
   }
   ```

   Make sure to replace `{slug}` with your actual FlowBlinq slug.

3. **Commit your changes** to the repository. Vercel will automatically deploy the changes.

This setup will allow requests to `/llms.txt` to be proxied to FlowBlinq's serve endpoint. If you have any questions or need further assistance, feel free to ask!
